(159, 39, 'why_roundhex', '<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-31" src="http://localhost:8888/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/pencil-timeline-narrow.png" alt="pencil-timeline-narrow" />\r\n<p class="p1">Round Hex is short for rounded hexagon—the shape of most modern-day pencils. When we first discovered the history of the pencil, the story resonated with us as it parallels the approach and work of Round Hex.</p>\r\n<a href="#">Read the whole story </a>'),
