INSERT INTO `rh_postmeta` (`meta_id`, `post_id`, `meta_key`, `meta_value`) VALUES
(382, 79, '_identity_design_story_1_step_gallery', 'field_54f630a5ed2a4'),
(383, 79, 'identity_design_story_2_identity_design_step', '<h4 class="p1">Examining Cultural Roots</h4>\r\n<p class="p1">After presenting our top three choices to the client, this simple “SQ” monogram emerged as the clear favorite. Having selected a mark that reflected Western calligraphic traditions more than Eastern, we decided to explore our options for striking more of a balance between the two. The square seals traditionally used by Chinese painters came to mind almost immediately. Careful explorations of texture and composition followed, producing a wide array of variations which we again narrowed down to our top three.</p>'),
(384, 79, '_identity_design_story_2_identity_design_step', 'field_54f5ee84bbe80'),
(385, 79, 'identity_design_story_2_step_gallery_0_gallery_photo', '71'),
(386, 79, '_identity_design_story_2_step_gallery_0_gallery_photo', 'field_54f630beed2a5'),
(387, 79, 'identity_design_story_2_step_gallery', '1'),
(388, 79, '_identity_design_story_2_step_gallery', 'field_54f630a5ed2a4'),
(389, 79, 'identity_design_story_3_identity_design_step', '<h4 class="p1">Color, Pattern, &amp; Font Selection</h4>\r\n<p class="p1">Having developed a graphic that spoke to the unique qualities of the Shanghai Quartet, our next move was to hand pick the fonts, colors, and patterns that would best support the quartet’s new graphic identity. GriffosFont was selected for the wordmark based on its old-world, hand-chiseled look; the tail on the Q was elongated to add to the unique character of the mark.</p>'),
(390, 79, '_identity_design_story_3_identity_design_step', 'field_54f5ee84bbe80'),
(391, 79, 'identity_design_story_3_step_gallery_0_gallery_photo', '73'),
(392, 79, '_identity_design_story_3_step_gallery_0_gallery_photo', 'field_54f630beed2a5'),
(393, 79, 'identity_design_story_3_step_gallery', '1'),
(394, 79, '_identity_design_story_3_step_gallery', 'field_54f630a5ed2a4'),
(395, 79, 'identity_design_story_4_identity_design_step', '<p class="p1">A Baroque background pattern was chosen based on the association of that era with the dawn of chamber music, and for its luxurious connotations. The colors—dark blue, ivory, and gold—were likewise chosen for their association in Western cultures with royalty and refinement, driving home the point that listening to a performance by the Shanghai Quartet has the power to whisk one away from the gritty details and worries of everyday life.</p>'),
(396, 79, '_identity_design_story_4_identity_design_step', 'field_54f5ee84bbe80'),
(397, 79, 'identity_design_story_4_step_gallery_0_gallery_photo', '72'),
(398, 79, '_identity_design_story_4_step_gallery_0_gallery_photo', 'field_54f630beed2a5'),
