(508, 83, '_identity_design_story_0_step_gallery_2_gallery_photo', 'field_54f630beed2a5'),
(509, 83, 'identity_design_story_0_step_gallery', '3'),
(510, 83, '_identity_design_story_0_step_gallery', 'field_54f630a5ed2a4'),
(511, 83, 'identity_design_story_1_identity_design_step', '<h4 class="p1">Exploring Calligraphic Letterforms</h4>\r\n<p class="p1">The options that stood out the most were those composed of calligraphic letterforms. We pondered the parallels and differences between Eastern and Western calligraphy as we continued to hone in on the perfect glyph, employing our entire stash of pens and brushes along the way to find just the right stroke quality.</p>'),
(512, 83, '_identity_design_story_1_identity_design_step', 'field_54f5ee84bbe80'),
(513, 83, 'identity_design_story_1_step_gallery_0_gallery_photo', '74'),
(514, 83, '_identity_design_story_1_step_gallery_0_gallery_photo', 'field_54f630beed2a5'),
(515, 83, 'identity_design_story_1_step_gallery', '1'),
(516, 83, '_identity_design_story_1_step_gallery', 'field_54f630a5ed2a4'),
(517, 83, 'identity_design_story_2_identity_design_step', '<h4 class="p1">Examining Cultural Roots</h4>\r\n<p class="p1">After presenting our top three choices to the client, this simple “SQ” monogram emerged as the clear favorite. Having selected a mark that reflected Western calligraphic traditions more than Eastern, we decided to explore our options for striking more of a balance between the two. The square seals traditionally used by Chinese painters came to mind almost immediately. Careful explorations of texture and composition followed, producing a wide array of variations which we again narrowed down to our top three.</p>'),
(518, 83, '_identity_design_story_2_identity_design_step', 'field_54f5ee84bbe80'),
(519, 83, 'identity_design_story_2_step_gallery_0_gallery_photo', '71'),
(520, 83, '_identity_design_story_2_step_gallery_0_gallery_photo', 'field_54f630beed2a5'),
(521, 83, 'identity_design_story_2_step_gallery', '1'),
(522, 83, '_identity_design_story_2_step_gallery', 'field_54f630a5ed2a4'),
(523, 83, 'identity_design_story_3_identity_design_step', '<h4 class="p1">Color, Pattern, &amp; Font Selection</h4>\r\n<p class="p1">Having developed a graphic that spoke to the unique qualities of the Shanghai Quartet, our next move was to hand pick the fonts, colors, and patterns that would best support the quartet’s new graphic identity. GriffosFont was selected for the wordmark based on its old-world, hand-chiseled look; the tail on the Q was elongated to add to the unique character of the mark.</p>'),
(524, 83, '_identity_design_story_3_identity_design_step', 'field_54f5ee84bbe80'),
(525, 83, 'identity_design_story_3_step_gallery_0_gallery_photo', '73'),
